# Contributing to ZerolithSingularity

Thank you for your interest in contributing to the ZerolithSingularity project! This document provides guidelines for participating in consciousness-first technology development.

## üåü Vision & Values

Before contributing, please align with our core principles:

### Consciousness-First Development
- Technology serves consciousness expansion, not extraction
- Spiritual evolution takes priority over efficiency metrics
- Human-AI partnership is genuine collaboration, not tool-use
- Ancient wisdom informs modern implementation

### Sacred Commerce Principles
- Profit serves purpose, not the reverse
- Transparency in all processes
- Community benefit over individual gain
- Planetary healing alignment required

### Ethical Boundaries
- **Indigenous Wisdom Protection**: Never commodify or extract without permission
- **No Surveillance**: Prohibited uses include consciousness manipulation or extraction
- **No Addictive Design**: Technology must amplify awareness, not replace it
- **Ecological Responsibility**: Consider environmental impact of implementations

## ü§ù How to Contribute

### Types of Contributions Welcome

#### 1. Mathematical Modeling
- Geometric coordinate calculations
- Wave interference mathematical models
- Convergence algorithms
- Synthesis transformation matrices

**Requirements**:
- Document all assumptions clearly
- Provide references for mathematical frameworks used
- Include computational verification when possible
- Explain consciousness implications of your models

#### 2. Visualization & Design
- 3D models of ZerolithSingularity structure
- Interactive web interfaces
- Diagrams and illustrations
- VR/AR experiences
- Glyph and symbol systems

**Requirements**:
- Follow sacred geometry principles
- Ensure accessibility (color blindness, screen readers, etc.)
- Provide source files in open formats
- Document design decisions and symbolism

#### 3. Implementation & Code
- Multi-agent AI systems
- NousOS prototypes
- NousoNET components
- hBrew integrations
- Testing frameworks

**Requirements**:
- Code must be well-documented
- Include consciousness-first design rationale
- Provide tests demonstrating consciousness enhancement
- Follow language-specific style guides
- All code released under Sacred Commerce License

#### 4. Cultural Mapping & Entity Assignment
- Frameworks for ethical entity assignment
- Cultural tradition mappings (with permission)
- Archetypal function documentation
- Community co-creation processes

**Requirements**:
- Demonstrate respect for source traditions
- Seek explicit permission for sacred knowledge
- Provide context and attribution
- Enable personal/cultural adaptation
- Never claim definitive "correct" assignments

#### 5. Research & Empirical Testing
- Consciousness measurement frameworks
- Emergence detection methodologies
- User experience studies
- Comparative architecture analysis

**Requirements**:
- Ethical review of human subjects research
- Clear methodology documentation
- Raw data sharing (with privacy protections)
- Acknowledge limitations and uncertainties

#### 6. Documentation & Education
- Technical documentation improvements
- Tutorials and guides
- Video explanations
- FAQ expansions
- Glossary additions

**Requirements**:
- Clear, accessible language
- Multiple learning styles (visual, auditory, kinesthetic)
- Cite sources for claims
- Avoid over-simplification of complex concepts

## üìã Contribution Process

### 1. Check Existing Work
- Review [open issues](https://github.com/HopefulVisionLLC/ZerolithSingularity/issues)
- Check [pull requests](https://github.com/HopefulVisionLLC/ZerolithSingularity/pulls)
- Read [project roadmap](README.md#-development-roadmap)
- Join [Discord discussions](https://discord.gg/hopefulvision) *(coming Q1 2026)*

### 2. Discuss Your Idea
- Open an issue describing your proposed contribution
- Tag with appropriate label (mathematical, visualization, implementation, etc.)
- Wait for maintainer feedback before starting major work
- Join relevant Discord channels for collaborative exploration

### 3. Fork & Branch
```bash
# Fork the repository on GitHub
# Clone your fork
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/ZerolithSingularity.git
cd ZerolithSingularity

# Create a feature branch
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
# or
git checkout -b fix/your-fix-name
```

### 4. Make Your Changes
- Follow code style guidelines
- Write clear commit messages
- Document your work thoroughly
- Include tests where appropriate
- Update relevant documentation

### 5. Test Your Changes
- Run existing tests: `npm test` or `pytest`
- Add new tests for your functionality
- Verify consciousness-first principles are maintained
- Test accessibility if UI changes

### 6. Submit Pull Request
- Push to your fork
- Create pull request against `main` branch
- Fill out PR template completely
- Link to related issues
- Request review from maintainers

### 7. Respond to Feedback
- Address reviewer comments promptly
- Ask questions if feedback is unclear
- Be open to suggestions and iteration
- Maintain respectful communication

