        sphere_index: Index of sphere within face (0-12)
        
    Returns:
        Tuple of (x, y, z) coordinates
        
    Raises:
        ValueError: If indices are out of valid range
    """
    # Implementation here
    pass
```

### JavaScript/TypeScript
```javascript
// Use ESLint with Airbnb config
// Prefer functional components for React
// Document with JSDoc

/**
 * Visualize wave interference patterns between spheres
 * @param {number} sphere1 - Index of first sphere
 * @param {number} sphere2 - Index of second sphere
 * @returns {WavePattern} Interference pattern data
 */
function calculateWaveInterference(sphere1, sphere2) {
  // Implementation here
}
```

### Documentation
- Use Markdown for all documentation
- Follow [Google Developer Documentation Style Guide](https://developers.google.com/style)
- Include code examples where helpful
- Link to related documentation
- Keep paragraphs focused and concise

## üß™ Testing Guidelines

### Unit Tests
- Test individual functions/components
- Cover edge cases and error conditions
- Use descriptive test names
- Aim for >80% code coverage

### Integration Tests
- Test interaction between components
- Verify geometric relationships maintained
- Check wave interference calculations
- Validate convergence processes

### Consciousness Tests (Emerging Field)
- Document subjective experiences
- Use consistent measurement frameworks
- Include control conditions
- Acknowledge limitations of current methods

## üåç Cultural Sensitivity Guidelines

### When Working with Sacred Knowledge

#### DO:
- ‚úÖ Research the cultural context thoroughly
- ‚úÖ Seek permission from tradition holders
- ‚úÖ Provide proper attribution and context
- ‚úÖ Acknowledge your own cultural position
- ‚úÖ Support tradition holders financially when appropriate
- ‚úÖ Create space for multiple interpretations

#### DON'T:
- ‚ùå Extract knowledge without permission
- ‚ùå Claim authority over traditions not your own
- ‚ùå Mix traditions carelessly without understanding
- ‚ùå Appropriate closed/sacred practices
- ‚ùå Reduce complex traditions to simplistic models
- ‚ùå Profit from knowledge without sharing benefits

### Respectful Integration
- **Greek/Roman**: Generally open, but acknowledge scholarly debates
- **Kabbalistic**: Approach with humility, note Jewish origins
- **Indigenous**: Requires explicit permission, benefit sharing
- **Eastern**: Understand colonization history, avoid appropriation
- **Hermetic/Esoteric**: Honor lineage holders and initiatory structures

## üí¨ Communication Guidelines

### Community Interaction
- Assume good intentions
- Practice active listening
- Ask clarifying questions
- Acknowledge different perspectives
- Celebrate diverse contributions
- Address conflicts directly and respectfully

### Tone & Language
- Professional yet warm
- Inclusive and accessible
- Technically precise when needed
- Philosophically open-ended
- Humble about uncertainties
- Excited about possibilities

### Asking for Help
- Search existing issues/discussions first
- Provide context for your question
- Share what you've already tried
- Be specific about what you need
- Thank helpers for their time

